description: Scott Bernard and a small fleet from Admiral Rick Hunter's Robotech Expeditionary Force return to Earth, only to find it devastated by the Invid Regis. They quickly come under attack, and Scott is forced to watch as the entire fleet is devastated by Invid forces. Crash landing on Earth, he runs into young Rand, a scavenger more interested in running than fighting. Still, Rand sees his best chance for survival in the war-torn world is with the experienced military man, and Scott sees his best chance to complete his mission and contact Admiral Rick Hunter is with a knowledgeable guide. Together, with their cyclone veritech armors, they set off across the hostile landscape.
name: The Invid Invasion

description: This 5-part storyline will finally reveal many secrets of Darkhawk's origin that have been gnawing at readers since the series' debut (perhaps the face behind the mask?), culminating in a double-sized 25th issue extravaganza! As an added bonus, when all five covers are put together, they form an incredible Darkhawk collage!
name: Return To Forever (Part 1): Buried Vengence

description: St. Johnny, Code Blue and Darkhawk do battle, as Arthur Vale escapes from FBI custody.
name: Return To Forever (Part 3):  Betrayal!
Return To Forever (Part 5): Death And Life

description:
Shattered Fates Part One: The Fury of Time. Darkhawk and the New Warriors battle ghosts sent by Zarrko the Tomorrow Man.

Beyond the Law! Savage Steel turns on the Cabal.
name: Shattered Fates (Part 1):  The Fury Of Time

description:
Shattered Fates Part Two. Zarrko offers the New Warriors the opportunity to fix their pasts.

A Tale of the Cabal. The Cabal avoids being killed in prison.
name: Shattered Fates (Part 2): The Future Is Prologue

description: Shattered Fates Part Three: Time to Kill. In order to go back in time to undo certain events, Darkhawk, and special guest-stars, the New Warriors, complete their mission in Chronopolis for Zarrko. Now, they want him to fullfll his nd of the bargain, and he's delighted to send them back in time -- and let them rot there!
name: Shattered Fates (Part 3): Time To Kill

description: Shattered Fates Part Four: Past Shock starring Darkhawk, Zarrko, Servitor, Night Thrasher, Nova, Namorita, Speedball, Firestar, Silhouette, Jon, Jason, Allegra Bazin, Philippe Bazin, Lodestone, Chord, Mr. Fantastic, Thing, Human Torch, Invisible Woman, Tai, and Justice. The New Warriors defeat Zarrko and Darkhawk gains his flying powers.
name: Shattered Fates (Part 4):  Past Shock

description: The Goddess, a near-omnipotent being, has pacified the Earth with her powers. But all this removed potential for evil has to go somewhere. It coalesces into a humanoid being that decides to give Darkhawk a good pounding.
name: The Evil Unleashed

description: Darkhawk volunteers to go into space with many other heroes to rescue shanghaied and brainwashed colleagues. The sheer scale of what he is doing causes much doubt and soul-searching for our hero.
name: Punch-Out On the Intergalactic Express!

description: Savage Steel returns, revamped and more powerful, to help Darkhawk bust up a terrorist operation! Also: Broderick Bazin continues his revenge on the Powell family, edging closer to the brink of insanity.
name: Savage Return

description: Darkhawk and Venom come to blows in the conclusion of this 3-part storyline! Then the fate of Chris' dad is revealed at last. This issue leads into the 4-part "Amulert Quest" beginning next month!
name: Operation Symbiote (Part 3): The Greater Evil!
The Bitter Truth;  The Shaper Of Things To Come

description: The reasons for Darkhawk's disappearance are finally explained, and details about the deal he made with Portal are revealed. But does it matter? Portal is mere seconds away from being executed by the Mahari! Crossover note: Events from this issue lead directly into this month's Amazing Spider-Man: Friends & Enemies limited series!
name: Revelations And Revenge

description: Still recovering from the disease that put him out of the series for several issues, Darkhawk is back! Portal needs help defeating the revenge-crazed Mahari, but is Darkhawk up to it? Events in this issue lead up to Darkhawk #50!
name: A Hawk Supreme (Part 1): Overhawk

description: The Mahari want revenge on Darkhawk and Portal -- and a brand new villian wants to get in on the action! Newcomer Overhawk works at the vanguard for the Mahari's crazed mission to destroy Earth. But Portal may have to avert their plans on his own, unless a convalescing Darkhawk can make it to the fight on time!
name: A Hawk Supreme (Part 2): Lives In The Balance

description: The startling, 48-page finale! In the conclusion of "A Hawk Supreme," Darkhawk and Portal end this mini-saga by facing the twin threat of the vengeful Mahari and Overhawk. Plus :Darkhawk becomes one again with his other self, Chris Powell!
name: A Hawk Supreme (Part 3): Glory!
